{
  "answer": "**1. In-Depth User Understanding:** Understanding the human tendency toward falsehood, the scriptures explicitly forbid superstitions such as seeking decisions through divining arrows, declaring them a grave disobedience and a defilement from the work of Satan [1, 2].\n\n**2. Robust and Enduring Framework:** This prohibition is built upon the steadfast foundation that ultimate benefit and harm rest solely in the hands of Allah [3]. Surah Yunus 10:107 establishes this enduring truth by stating that if God touches someone with adversity, only He can remove it, and if He intends good, absolutely no one can repel His bounty [3]. \n\n**3. Elegant and Lucid Presentation:** The verses eloquently clarify this reality by criticizing those who believe in superstition (*jibt*) and false objects of worship [4]. They clearly present that anything worshipped or relied upon besides God possesses zero power to cause harm or bring benefit [5]. \n\n**4. Seamless and Accessible Experience:** This straightforward guidance provides a clear and accessible path for believers by directing their complete reliance toward God [6]. It teaches that superstitious entities and false partners cannot even protect or help themselves, whereas Allah is the ultimate protector and ally of the righteous [6, 7].",
